🇩🇪 Germany now has the most last place finishes in the Grand Final (5) since the "Big 4" (as it was) began in 2004. #Eurovision
⬇️ Germany's last place finish in the Grand Final was the first time 21st in the running order has produced the country with the fewest points. #Eurovision
🔝 12th place in the running order is now statistically the best pace to perform in the Grand Final, with an average finishing position of 10th. 17th has produced the most winners with 7. #Eurovision
🇸🇪 Loreen's 2nd place finish in the semi final this year extends Sweden's lead in the amount of top three finishes in #Eurovision semi finals to 9.
🇦🇺 Australia have now won 3/7 semi finals in which they've competed. That's one behind record holders Sweden, but the Scandi nation have taken part in 7 more semis than the Aussies. #Eurovision
🎉 Four countries now hold the record for most qualifications from the semi finals: 🇬🇷🇳🇴🇸🇪🇺🇦 with 13. Only Ukraine has a 100% qualifying rate. #Eurovision
🇲🇰 This was the first year in which North Macedonia didn't feature in a semi final. Estonia and Slovenia are now the only countries to perform in 19 #Eurovision semi finals.
🏆 2023 was the first year in which last in the running order produced the winner in both semi finals #Eurovision
🇲🇹 After Malta's NQ, both 2nd and 3rd in the semi final running order now have the joint worst qualifying rate with 35.29%. #Eurovision
🇸🇲 Piqued Jacks were the first artist to finish last in a semi final performing 12th in the running order. #Eurovision
